Count 1 - Possess THC with Intent to Deliver - Guilty plea.  Convicted.  State moves to dismiss and read in count 2 and 3, 2 cts. Possess THC with Intent to Deliver.  Motion granted.  Defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total of seven (7) years.  Three (3) years initial confinement, followed by four (4) years extended supervision, imposed and stayed.  Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for five (5) years.  Conditions of probation are:
1) Spend four (4) months in jail, under the Huber Law, to commence immediately;
2) Pay $10,000.00 fine, plus costs, total of $22,668.00;
3) Assessment/treatment/counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
4) Provide DNA sample;
5) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC.
Defendant is given credit for fifty-three (53) days time already served.    
Cash bail applied to fine and costs.  
Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights. 
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief.  
Ineligible Voting Notice & Acknowledgment.  
